    {
        "content": "<p>hiSandog <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/issues/13790#issuecomment-4874801151\">commented</a> on <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/issues/13790\">issue #13790</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>This seems like a case where an optimization pass produces IR that is legal in the mid-end but not supported by the selected x86_64 lowering path. A reduced CLIF test plus a verifier/check after the relevant optimization would help pin down whether the pass should be target-aware or the backend should handle the new shape. The regression should assert a normal compile error or successful lowering, never a backend-internal unsupported IR failure.<br>\n</p>\n</blockquote>",
